      <lg type="edition">
<l>añcuvaru marapiṉ veñciṉam puyalē</l>
<l>ṟaṇaṅkuṭai yaravi ṉaruntalai tumiya</l>
<l>niṉṟukāṇ paṉṉa nīṇmalai miḷirak</l>
<l>kuṉṟutū veṟiyu maravam pōla</l>
<l>muraceḻun tiraṅkun tāṉaiyoṭu talaicceṉ</l>
<l>ṟaraicupaṭak kaṭakku muraicā ṟōṉṟaṉiṉ</l>
<l>ṉuḷḷi vanta vōṅkunilaip paricileṉ</l>
<l>vaḷḷiyai yātaliṉ vaṇaṅkuva ṉivaṉeṉak</l>
<l>koḷḷā māntar koṭumai kūṟaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉuḷḷiyatu muṭittōy maṉṟa muṉṉāṭ</l>
<l>kaiyuḷ ḷatupōṟ kāṭṭi vaḻināṭ</l>
<l>poyyoṭu niṉṟa puṟanilai varutta</l>
<l>nāṇā yāyiṉu nāṇak kūṟiye</l>
<l>ṉuṇaṅku cennā vaṇaṅka vēttip</l>
<l>pāṭap pāṭap pāṭupukaḻ koṇṭaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉāṭukoḷ viyaṉmārpu toḻutaṉeṉ paḻiccic</l>
<l>celva lattai yāṉē vaikalum</l>
<l>valci yiṉmaiyiṉ vayiṉvayiṉ māṟi</l>
<l>yilleli maṭinta tolcuvar varaippiṟ</l>
<l>pāa liṉmaiyiṟ palpāṭu cuvaittu</l>
<l>mulaikkōṇ maṟanta putalvaṉoṭu</l>
<l>maṉaittolain tiruntaveṉ vāṇutaṟ paṭarntē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O appearance worthy of words who wins, so that kings fall, (6)</l>
<l>when going at the head of [your] army where drums rise [and] sound (5)</l>
<l>similar to the sound that widely attacks the hills (4)</l>
<l>so that tall mountains roll over as if one had seen [them] standing, (3)</l>
<l>so that the heads difficult [to approach] of frightful snakes are cut off, (2)</l>
<l>[the sound] of hot angry thunder claps in the rain, according to fearful custom, (1)</l>
<l>I am a gift-seeker of high standing who has come remembering you. (6) </l>
<l>While people who do not understand talk cruelty (9)</l>
<l>“because you are generous this one will bow”, (8)</l>
<l>you have finalised your thinking indeed. (10a-c)</l>
<l>As on a former day you showed [your] hand as if something was inside it, (10d-11c)</l>
<l>on the following, day even though you are not ashamed (11d+13ab)</l>
<l>of [my] suffering in standing outside where I stand with [your] falsehood (12)</l>
<l>  [I], having talked so that [you] would be ashamed, (13cd)</l>
<l>having praised so that my subtle refined tongue is tormented, (14)</l>
<l>having adored as one who worships the murderous wide chest (16)</l>
<l>of you who take the praise of [my] singing, while singing [and] singing, (15)</l>
<l>I will go, (17a-c)</l>
<l>– setting our for my [girl with] bright forehead who sits forelorn in the house (22)</l>
<l>with a son who has forgotten to take the breast (21)</l>
<l>after having tasted many times the absence of milk, (20)</l>
<l>within the bounds of ancient walls where the house rats droop, (19)</l>
<l>changing from side to side in the absence of food daily. (17f-18)</l>
</lg>
